Ahh got it—that’s a **different requirement** 👍
You don’t want one rule with optional fields… you want **completely different behavior per environment**:

* **DEV → Delete blobs**
* **PROD → Archive blobs (no delete)**

👉 This is the correct way to do it: **separate rules using conditional logic**

---

# ✅ **Clean Terraform Solution (Env-based Rules)**

## **1. Locals**

```hcl id="4p8x1n"
variable "environment" {
  type = string
}

locals {
  is_dev  = var.environment == "dev"
  is_prod = var.environment == "prod"
}
```

---

## **2. Lifecycle Policy with Conditional Rules**

```hcl id="1n6zqz"
resource "azurerm_storage_management_policy" "lifecycle" {
  storage_account_id = azurerm_storage_account.example.id

  # ✅ DEV → DELETE RULE
  dynamic "rule" {
    for_each = local.is_dev ? [1] : []

    content {
      name    = "delete-old-data-dev"
      enabled = true

      filters {
        blob_types   = ["blockBlob"]
        prefix_match = ["archivepoc/"]
      }

      actions {
        base_blob {
          delete_after_days_since_modification_greater_than = 30
        }
      }
    }
  }

  # ✅ PROD → ARCHIVE RULE
  dynamic "rule" {
    for_each = local.is_prod ? [1] : []

    content {
      name    = "archive-old-data-prod"
      enabled = true

      filters {
        blob_types   = ["blockBlob"]
        prefix_match = ["archivepoc/"]
      }

      actions {
        base_blob {
          tier_to_archive_after_days_since_modification_greater_than = 365
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

---

# 🧠 **Behavior**

| Environment         | Action                 |
| ------------------- | ---------------------- |
| **dev**             | Delete after 30 days   |
| **prod**            | Archive after 365 days |
| **test (if added)** | No rule unless defined |

